THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS AND THEIR LICENSES
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

This project uses several third-party open-source components. Below is a
non-exhaustive list of major dependencies and their licenses. The full list
with exact versions is available via each module's `go.mod` or
`requirements.txt`.

Backend (Go 1.22+):
  - github.com/gin-gonic/gin               MIT
  - github.com/nats-io/nats.go            Apache-2.0
  - github.com/redis/go-redis             BSD-2-Clause
  - github.com/jackc/pgx/v5               MIT
  - github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5          MIT
  - github.com/google/uuid                BSD-3-Clause
  - github.com/gorilla/websocket          BSD-2-Clause
  - github.com/prometheus/client_golang   Apache-2.0
  - golang.org/x/crypto                   BSD-3-Clause
  - google.golang.org/protobuf            BSD-3-Clause

AI/ML (Python 3.12+):
  - fastapi                               MIT
  - uvicorn                               BSD-3-Clause
  - pydantic                              MIT
  - nats-py                               Apache-2.0
  - redis-py                              MIT
  - asyncpg                               Apache-2.0
  - httpx                                 BSD-3-Clause
  - structlog                             Apache-2.0 / MIT
  - numpy                                 BSD-3-Clause
  - pandas                                BSD-3-Clause

Frontend (TypeScript):
  - react, react-dom                      MIT
  - lucide-react                          ISC
  - recharts                              MIT
  - vite                                  MIT

Infrastructure (Docker images):
  - postgres / timescale/timescaledb      PostgreSQL License (BSD-style)
  - redis                                 BSD-3-Clause
  - nats                                  Apache-2.0
  - ollama                                MIT
  - traefik                               MIT
  - prometheus, node-exporter, postgres-exporter  Apache-2.0
  - redis_exporter                        MIT
  - grafana                               AGPL-3.0 (only the Grafana image, not the dashboards)

